main event: Several unidentified objects were observed in the sky over Los Angeles, California on November 29, 1966 for about 20 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were observed from the ground and the report notes that the sighting was 'Ground-Visual'.
The Air Force requested that the witness complete an additional form (FTD Form 16) to provide more information for their evaluation, indicating they did not have sufficient data to draw a conclusion.
The report states that there was 'INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR EVALUATION' in the conclusion.
The Air Force letter references a 'UFO Observation' on November 29, 1966, suggesting this was part of the Project Blue Book investigation of UFO reports.
The handwritten notes on the third page of the report describe a hovering, luminous object that suddenly shot up into the sky at high speed, with a distinct humming sound.
